** CURL STORY MOMENT**
I used to hate my curls when I was a kid. I‚Äôve always been the only one with curls in my family & so no one of my parents could help me understand how to treat them; plus, in the 90s & 00s here in Italy there weren‚Äôt good products for curls cause the majority of Italians don‚Äôt have this kind of hair ü§¶üèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è hairstylists were practically scared when they saw me enter in one of their stores &, as you can imagine, they were totally helpless to me üôÑ
Also, during high school kids used to joke me on my hair, so this made me feel like inappropriate...
Just few years ago, like 4-5, finally the ‚Äúcurl culture‚Äù landed in Italy too & I heard of bio products & bio perfumeries that sold these products and when I started my transition I‚Äôve seen my hair passing from being dry, with no form, no volume & opaque to being super voluminous, thicker, so soft and defined üíñüë©üèª‚Äçü¶±
If I could talk to my past self I would say her that our hair was worthing all those difficulties because we have the most beautiful hair in the world & that lionesses have manes, not hair ü¶Åüß°
.
.
